description:
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England (HEE) exists for one reason only: to support the delivery of excellent healthcare and health improvement to the patients and public of England by ensuring that the workforce of today and tomorrow has the right numbers, skills, values and behaviours, at the right time and in the right place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The National Advancing Practice programme is part of the Department of Education &amp; Quality. We are working collaboratively across healthcare to develop safe and effective practitioners who you would trust to care for your loved one at the level of an advanced practitioner and above, whatever they do, wherever they work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to undertake the Programme Accreditation Lead role to support the Centre for Advancing Practice Lead who is responsible for developing and operationalising the Centre functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder be required to act in a leadership role, developing and implementing accreditation policy and processes for the Centre for Advancing Practice. The postholder will produce high quality documents on behalf of the Centre, manage key relationships with stakeholders and represent the accreditation team in national forums.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will advise HEE colleagues and external organisations about Advanced Practice programme accreditation requirements, policy, and process. Furthermore, the postholder will produce high quality reports, be responsible for ensuring the quality management of the work of the accreditation team and for delivery within operating budgets. The postholder will have some line management responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to work on a high profile and exciting workforce transformation programme, in a supportive and busy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this role you should be educated to master’s level or have equivalent knowledge and skills acquired through experience. You must have a thorough understanding of higher education programmes and the Advanced Practice agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that flexibility is required and the postholder may be required to undertake work commensurate to their grading on a different project/programme if this project should come to an end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 8a with a full-time starting salary of £45,753, with a pay step increase after 5 years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close this vacancy early if we receive sufficient applications for the role. Therefore, if you are interested, please submit your application as early as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard.Collier@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Harjinder.Kaur-Heer@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
